  "prompt": "A bag contains 5 white, 7 red and 8 black balls. If four balls are drawn one by one without replacement, what is the probability of getting all white balls?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) First, let's calculate the total number of balls in the bag:\n   \u2022 5 white balls\n   \u2022 7 red balls\n   \u2022 8 black balls\n   \u2022 Total = 20 balls\n\n2) To get all white balls, we need to draw 4 white balls in a row without replacement\n\n3) To calculate this probability, we'll use the multiplication rule\n\n4) First ball draw:\n   \u2022 Probability of drawing a white ball = 5/20\n\n5) Second ball draw:\n   \u2022 After drawing the first white ball, only 4 white balls and 19 total balls remain\n   \u2022 Probability of drawing a white ball = 4/19\n\n6) Third ball draw:\n   \u2022 Now 3 white balls and 18 total balls remain\n   \u2022 Probability of drawing a white ball = 3/18\n\n7) Fourth ball draw:\n   \u2022 Now 2 white balls and 17 total balls remain\n   \u2022 Probability of drawing a white ball = 2/17\n\n8) Total probability is the product of these individual probabilities:\n   \u2022 (5/20) * (4/19) * (3/18) * (2/17)\n\n9) Let's calculate:\n   \u2022 = (5 * 4 * 3 * 2) / (20 * 19 * 18 * 17)\n   \u2022 = 120 / (116280)\n   \u2022 = 1 / 969\n\nThe probability is 1/969.",
